---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="The AI Sanctions File — 14 Real Court Orders"
  description="14 real court orders sanctioning lawyers for AI errors — and the firm protocols that would have prevented each. PDF + editable policy template. $19."
>
  <article class="aie-tripwire">
    <div class="container">

      <header class="aie-tripwire__header">
        <p class="label"><a href="/ai-ethics">Ethics Safe AI Use for Law Firms</a></p>
        <h1 class="aie-tripwire__title">The AI Sanctions File</h1>
        <p class="aie-tripwire__price">$19</p>
        <p class="aie-tripwire__sub">
          14 real court orders sanctioning lawyers for AI errors — and the firm
          protocols that would have prevented each. PDF + editable policy template.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <div class="aie-tripwire__body prose">
        <p>
          Every entry includes the case, the court, the specific AI failure, the
          sanction imposed, and the written protocol that closes the gap. Not
          summaries — the actual orders, with the language courts used.
        </p>
        <p>
          The editable policy template is formatted for immediate firm use: drop
          in your firm name, assign an attorney supervisor, and you have a
          documented AI-use protocol you can show a carrier, a client, or a court.
        </p>
        <p>
          If a new sanctions order drops in your circuit after purchase, you get
          the updated file at no charge for 12 months.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="aie-tripwire__cta">
        <!-- LEMON SQUEEZY: replace href with $19 tripwire checkout URL -->
        <a href="https://kameir.lemonsqueezy.com/checkout/buy/TRIPWIRE-ID" class="btn btn--primary">
          Get the Sanctions File — $19
        </a>
        <p class="aie-tripwire__cta-note">
          Instant download. PDF + editable .docx policy template.
          Secure checkout via Lemon Squeezy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <div class="aie-tripwire__upsell">
        <p class="label">Want the full playbook?</p>
        <p>
          The <a href="/ai-ethics">Ethics Safe AI Use for Law Firms</a> playbook
          covers all 10 risk areas with checklists, clause libraries, and 12-month
          updates — starting at $49 for a single user.
          Your $19 purchase applies toward any tier at checkout.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="aie-tripwire__disclaimer">
        <em>Informational only. Not legal advice. Ethics rules vary by jurisdiction.</em><br>
        Christian Kameir &thinsp;·&thinsp; © 2026 Decentralized Publishing LLC. All rights reserved.
      </p>

    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
.aie-tripwire__header {
  padding-top: 4rem;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-m);
}

.aie-tripwire__title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.aie-tripwire__price {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.aie-tripwire__sub {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 520px;
}

.aie-tripwire__body {
  padding-block: var(--space-l);
  max-width: 560px;
  font-size: 0.97rem;
}

.aie-tripwire__cta {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 2rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-l);
}

.aie-tripwire__cta-note {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
  max-width: 320px;
}

.aie-tripwire__upsell {
  padding-block: var(--space-m);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 540px;
}

.aie-tripwire__upsell .label {
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

.aie-tripwire__disclaimer {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.7;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
}
</style>
